{"title_page": "John Mayers", "text_new": "{{short description|English cricketer}}\n{{for|the Barbadian Olympic sprinter|John Mayers (athlete)}}\n'''John Mayers''' (1801 &ndash; April 1865) was an English cricketer who played for [[Kent County Cricket Club|Kent]]. He was born in [[Benenden]] and died in [[Hawkhurst]].\n\nMayers made a single first-class appearance for Kent, in 1827, against [[Sussex County Cricket Club|Sussex]]. Batting in the tailend, he scored a duck in the first innings before being bowled out by [[William Lillywhite]], and a single run in the second innings, before being run out.\n\n==External links==\n*[https://cricketarchive.com/Archive/Players/37/37289/37289.html John Mayers] at Cricket Archive\n{{Use dmy dates|date=April 2020}}\n{{Use British English|date=September 2010}}\n\n{{Authority control}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Mayers, John}}\n[[Category:1801 births]]\n[[Category:1865 deaths]]\n[[Category:English cricketers]]\n[[Category:Kent cricketers]]\n[[Category:People from the Borough of Tunbridge Wells]]\n\n\n{{England-cricket-bio-1800s-stub}}\n", "text_old": "{{short description|English cricketer}}\n{{for|the Barbadian Olympic sprinter|John Mayers (athlete)}}\n'''John Mayers''' (1801 &ndash; April 1865) was an English cricketer who played for [[Kent County Cricket Club|Kent]]. He was born in [[Benenden]] and died in [[Hawkhurst]].\n\nMayers made a single first-class appearance for Kent, in 1827, against [[Sussex County Cricket Club|Sussex]]. Batting in the tailend, he scored a duck in the first innings before being bowled out by [[William Lillywhite]], and a single run in the second innings, before being run out.\n\n==External links==\n*[https://cricketarchive.com/Archive/Players/37/37289/37289.html John Mayers] at Cricket Archive\n{{Use dmy dates|date=September 2010}}\n{{Use British English|date=September 2010}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Mayers, John}}\n[[Category:1801 births]]\n[[Category:1865 deaths]]\n[[Category:English cricketers]]\n[[Category:Kent cricketers]]\n[[Category:People from the Borough of Tunbridge Wells]]\n{{England-cricket-bio-1800s-stub}}\n", "name_user": "Rich Farmbrough", "label": "safe", "comment": "\u2192\u200eExternal links:Update date format tag and add authority control template", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/John_Mayers"}
{"title_page": "Mayor of Gibraltar", "text_new": "{{Use British English|date=January 2014}}\n{{Infobox Political post\n|post            = Mayor\n|body            = Gibraltar\n|insignia        = Coat_of_Arms_of_the_Government_of_Gibraltar.svg\n|insigniasize    = 100px\n|insigniacaption = The Coat of arms of the Mayor of Gibraltar\n|nativename      =\n|image           = \n|incumbent       = [[John Gon\u00e7alves]]\n|incumbentsince  = 5 April 2019\n|style           = [[Worship (style)|His or Her Worship]]\n|residence       = [[Gibraltar City Hall]]\n|appointer       = [[Gibraltar Parliament]]\n|termlength      = One Year\n|formation       =\n|succession      = \n|inaugural       = [[Joshua Hassan]]\n|deputy          = \n|salary          = Unpaid (no salary)\n|website         =\n}}\n[[Worship (style)|His or Her Worship]] the '''Mayor of Gibraltar''' is the ceremonial official of the [[British overseas territories|British overseas territory]] of [[Gibraltar]]. The [[mayor]] is appointed by the [[Elections in Gibraltar|elected]] Members of [[Gibraltar Parliament|Parliament]]<ref name=con>[http://www.gibraltar.gov.gi/constitution/new_constitution/NewGibraltarConstitution.pdf Gibraltar Constitution Order 2006] {{webarchive |url=https://web.archive.org/web/20081121050613/http://www.gibraltar.gov.gi/constitution/new_constitution/NewGibraltarConstitution.pdf |date=21 November 2008 }}</ref> and the office is situated at [[Gibraltar City Hall|City Hall]] John Mackintosh Square. Since 4 April 2019, [[John Gon\u00e7alves]] has held the position of Mayor of Gibraltar, succeeding [[Kaiane Aldorino]].<ref>\n{{cite web\n | url = https://www.gbc.gi/news/new-mayor-john-goncalves-says-he-wants-give-young-people-voice\n | title = New Mayor John Gon\u00e7alves says he wants to give young people a voice\n | accessdate = 5 April 2019}}\n</ref>\n\n==History==\n[[File:Gibraltar City Hall 01.jpg|thumb|250px|left|Centrally situated at [[John Mackintosh Square]], opposite the [[Gibraltar Parliament]], the [[Gibraltar City Hall]] is the office of the Mayor of Gibraltar.]]\nSince its creation in 1921, the city council had a chairman. In 1955, upon request of the members of the city council, the post was renamed to mayor, and therefore, the mayor of Gibraltar was chosen from among the members of the council. [[Joshua Hassan]], the chairman of the city council at the time become the first mayor of Gibraltar.\n\n===1969 Constitution===\n{{Main|Gibraltar Constitution Order 1969}}\nThe city council disappeared when the new Gibraltar Constitution Order in Council was signed in 1969. However, the mayor of Gibraltar survived, but only with a ceremonial character, and was to be elected by the House of Assembly (later the Parliament).<ref name=\"old\">[http://www.who.int/idhl-rils/idhl/RUGib05002.pdf Gibraltar Constitution Order 1969]</ref> This meant that office was invariably taken by the [[List of Speakers of the Gibraltar Parliament|Speaker]] or a government minister.<ref name=may>[http://www.gibfocus.gi/details_headlines.php?id=2299 Changes in Mayorship of Gibraltar]{{dead link|date=January 2018 |bot=InternetArchiveBot |fix-attempted=yes }}</ref>\n\nThe [[Gibraltar Constitution Order 1969|1969 Constitution]] stated:<ref name=\"old\"/>\n\n{{cquote|A person elected to the office of Mayor shall hold office upon such terms and conditions, and shall perform such functions (being ceremonial functions of a civic character), as may be determined by the [[Governor of Gibraltar|Governor]], acting after consultation with the [[Gibraltar Council]].}}\n\n===2006 Constitution===\n{{Main|Gibraltar Constitution Order 2006}}\nFollowing the new [[Gibraltar Constitution Order 2006|2006 Constitution]], the mayor no longer had to be chosen from among the members of Parliament. Instead, the mayor is appointed by Parliament. The intention was to move to a new system whereby citizens from the community at large can be appointed mayor for a one-year period. The [[Government of Gibraltar]] announced that a deputy mayor would also be appointed for the same period and would take up the office of mayor the following year.<ref name=may/>\n\n==Appointment==\nThe mayor of Gibraltar is appointed by Parliament but no longer from within Parliament, and is to hold the position for a one-year period.<ref name=sur>[http://www.surinenglish.com/20080704/news/gibraltar/gibraltar-appoints-first-parliamentary-200807041104.html Sur in English - Gibraltar appoints its first non-parliamentary Mayor, Solomon Levy]</ref> As per the 2006 Constitution:<ref name=con/>\n\n{{cquote|A person elected to the office of Mayor shall hold office upon such terms and conditions, and shall perform such functions (being ceremonial functions of a civic character), as may be determined by the Parliament.}}\n\n===Deputy===\nA deputy mayor is at the same time appointed by Parliament for one year to assist and support the mayor in the discharge of mayoral duties, as well as to act as mayor when she or he is unable to participate in a civic event. The deputy will take office as mayor the following year and a new deputy appointed, and so on.<ref name=sur/><ref>{{Cite web |url=http://www.gibraltar.gi/locals/news.php?action=view_article&article=3378 |title=Gibraltar.gi - Who wants to be Mayor? |access-date=22 August 2009 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20110721031815/http://www.gibraltar.gi/locals/news.php?action=view_article&article=3378 |archive-date=21 July 2011 |url-status=dead }}</ref>\n\n==Duties==\nSince 1969, the mayor is not a political figure as his or her duties are entirely [[ceremony|ceremonial]] and [[civic engagement|civic]].<ref name=sur/> The posts of mayor and deputy mayor of Gibraltar are [[title of honor|honorific]] and thus unpaid.<ref name=may/>\n\n==List of mayors==\nThe following is a list of all the mayors of Gibraltar since the first tenure began in 1955:<ref>[http://www.gibfocus.gi/details_todaysnews.php?id=2991 Portraits of Gibraltar's 10 Mayors]{{dead link|date=January 2018 |bot=InternetArchiveBot |fix-attempted=yes }}</ref>\n\n{|class=\"wikitable\" style=\"text-align:center\"\n|-\n|\n|'''Picture'''\n|'''Name'''\n|'''Took Office'''\n|'''Left Office'''\n|-\n|1\n|[[File:Joshua Hassan.jpg|80px|The Hon. Sir Joshua A. Hassan]]\n|[[The Honourable|The Hon.]] [[Joshua Hassan|Sir Joshua Hassan]] [[Order of the British Empire|CBE]] [[Royal Victorian Order|MVO]] [[Queen's Counsel|QC]] [[Justice of the peace|JP]]\n|23 February 1955\n|2 June 1969\n|-\n|2\n|\n|The Hon. [[Colonel|Col.]] [[William Thompson (Gibraltar)|William Thompson]] OBE JP\n|2 June 1969\n|6 November 1970\n|-\n|3\n|\n|The Hon. [[Alfred Vasquez|Alfred J. Vasquez]] CBE MA\n|6 November 1970\n|22 April 1976\n|-\n|4\n|[[File:Investidura Adolfo Canepa como nuevo alcalde (7).jpg|80px|The Hon. Adolfo J. Canepa]]\n|The Hon. [[Adolfo Canepa|Adolfo J. Canepa]]\n|22 April 1976\n|31 December 1978\n|-\n|5\n|\n|The Hon. [[Horace Zammitt|Horace J. Zammit]]\n|1 January 1979\n|31 July 1979\n|-\n|6\n|\n|The Hon. [[Abraham Serfaty (Gibraltarian)|Abraham W. Serfaty]] CBE JP\n|1 August 1979\n|31 July 1988\n|-\n|7\n|\n|The Hon. [[Mari Montegriffo|Mari I. Montegriffo]]\n|1 August 1988\n|20 March 1995\n|-\n|8\n|\n|The Hon. [[Robert Mor]]\n|20 March 1995\n|31 July 1996\n|-\n|9\n|\n|[[Judge]] [[John Alcantara|John E. Alcantara]] CBE\n|1 August 1996\n|31 July 2004\n|-\n|10\n|\n|The Hon. [[Clive Beltran|Clive G. Beltran]]\n|1 August 2004\n|31 July 2008\n|-\n|11\n|[[File:Sol levy mayor.jpg|80px|Solomon Levy MBE, JP]]\n|[[Solomon Levy|Solomon 'Momy' Levy]]\n|1 August 2008\n|31 July 2009\n|-\n|12\n|[[File:Olga zammitt.jpg|80px|Olga Zammitt, OBE, JP]]\n|[[Olga Zammitt]] OBE, JP\n|1 August 2009\n|31 July 2010\n|-\n|13\n|[[File:Tony Lombard (cropped).jpg|80px|Anthony Lombard]]\n|[[Anthony Lombard|Anthony J P Lombard]] Ll.B.\n|1 August 2010\n|31 July 2011\n|-\n|14\n|[[File:Julio Alcantara.jpg|80px|Julio Alcantara]]\n|[[Julio Alcantara]] \n|1 August 2011\n|31 July 2012\n|-\n|15\n|[[File:MayorTable.JPG|80px|Anthony Lima]]\n|[[Anthony Lima]]\n|1 August 2012\n|31 July 2014\n|-\n|4\n|[[File:Investidura Adolfo Canepa como nuevo alcalde (7).jpg|80px|The Hon. Adolfo J. Canepa]]\n|The Hon. [[Adolfo Canepa|Adolfo J. Canepa]]\n|1 August 2014\n|31 July 2017\n|-\n|16\n|[[File:Freedom of the City - Kaiane Aldorino - September 2011.jpg|80px|Kaiane Lopez]]\n|[[Kaiane Aldorino]]\n|1 August 2017\n|4 April 2019\n|-\n|16\n|\n|[[John Gon\u00e7alves]]\n|4 April 2019\n|Incumbent\n|-\n|}\n\n==References==\n{{Commons category|Mayors of Gibraltar}}\n{{Reflist}}\n\n{{Mayors of Gibraltar}}\n{{Gibraltar topics}}\n{{Authority control}}\n\n{{Use dmy dates|date=April 2020}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Mayor Of Gibraltar}}\n[[Category:Mayors of Gibraltar| ]]\n[[Category:Gibraltar-related lists]]\n", "text_old": "{{Use British English|date=January 2014}}\n{{Infobox Political post\n|post            = Mayor\n|body            = Gibraltar\n|insignia        = Coat_of_Arms_of_the_Government_of_Gibraltar.svg\n|insigniasize    = 100px\n|insigniacaption = The Coat of arms of the Mayor of Gibraltar\n|nativename      =\n|image           = \n|incumbent       = [[John Gon\u00e7alves]]\n|incumbentsince  = 5 April 2019\n|style           = [[Worship (style)|His or Her Worship]]\n|residence       = [[Gibraltar City Hall]]\n|appointer       = [[Gibraltar Parliament]]\n|termlength      = One Year\n|formation       =\n|succession      = \n|inaugural       = [[Joshua Hassan]]\n|deputy          = \n|salary          = Unpaid (no salary)\n|website         =\n}}\n[[Worship (style)|His or Her Worship]] the '''Mayor of Gibraltar''' is the ceremonial official of the [[British overseas territories|British overseas territory]] of [[Gibraltar]]. The [[mayor]] is appointed by the [[Elections in Gibraltar|elected]] Members of [[Gibraltar Parliament|Parliament]]<ref name=con>[http://www.gibraltar.gov.gi/constitution/new_constitution/NewGibraltarConstitution.pdf Gibraltar Constitution Order 2006] {{webarchive |url=https://web.archive.org/we