y:Years of the 21st century in Wales]]\n[[Category:2015 in the United Kingdom|*Wales]]\n", "name_user": "John of Reading", "label": "safe", "comment": "\u2192\u200eSport:Typo fixing, replaced: teams highest \u2192 team's highest", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/2015_in_Wales"}
{"title_page": "Ismism", "text_new": "{{Use British English|date=January 2014}}\n{{Use dmy dates|date=January 2014}}\n{{More references|date=October 2012}}\n{{Infobox album\n| name       = Ismism\n| type       = studio\n| artist     = [[Godley & Creme]]\n| cover      = Godley ismism.jpg\n| border     = yes\n| alt        =\n| released   = October 1981\n| recorded   = April\u2013May 1980\n| venue      =\n| studio     =\n| genre      = [[Pop rock]], [[New wave music|new wave]], [[synthpop]]\n| length     = 44:02\n| label      = [[Polydor]]\n| producer   = [[Kevin Godley]], [[Lol Creme]]\n| prev_title = [[Freeze Frame (Godley & Creme album)|Freeze Frame]]\n| prev_year  = 1979\n| next_title = [[Birds of Prey (Godley & Creme album)|Birds of Prey]]\n| next_year  = 1983\n| misc       = {{Singles\n | name        = Ismism\n | type        = studio\n | single1     = [[Under Your Thumb]]\n | single1date = 1981\n | single2     = [[Wedding Bells (Godley & Creme song)|Wedding Bells]]\n | single2date = 1981\n | single3     = Snack Attack\n | single3date = 1982\n}}\n{{Extra album cover\n | header  = US cover\n | type    = studio\n | cover   = Godley snack.jpg\n | border  =\n | alt     =\n | caption = The US cover of '''''Snack Attack'''''\n}}\n}}\n{{Album ratings\n| rev1      = [[Allmusic]]\n| rev1Score =  {{Rating|2|5}} [{{Allmusic|class=album|id=r39065|pure_url=yes}} link]\n}}\n'''''Ismism''''' is the fourth album by English band [[Godley & Creme]]. The album was released in the US under the name '''''Snack Attack'''''.\n\nIt spawned two UK top 10 singles, \"[[Under Your Thumb]]\" and \"[[Wedding Bells (Godley & Creme song)|Wedding Bells]]\".<ref name=\"Chart Stats - Godley And Creme\">{{cite web|url=https://www.officialcharts.com/artist/19218/godley-and-creme/ |title=The Official Charts Company - Godley And Creme |publisher=[[Official Charts Company]] |accessdate=23 December 2008 }}</ref>\n\nThe album cover originally was in white with the title spelt out via holes in the cover which showed a contrasting colour beneath. Later versions used coloured dots instead of holes. An alternative version of the cover featured a black background.\n\n''Ismism'' was reissued on CD in 2004 under ''Ismism... Plus'' name (with other Godley & Creme albums) with singles' b-sides as bonus tracks.\n\n==Track listing==\n\nAll songs composed by [[Kevin Godley]] and [[Lol Creme]].\n\n# \"Snack Attack\" \u2013 7:07\n# \"[[Under Your Thumb]]\" \u2013 4:40\n# \"Joey's Camel\" \u2013 5:23\n# \"The Problem\" \u2013 4:06\n# \"Ready for Ralph\" \u2013 2:20\n# \"[[Wedding Bells (Godley & Creme song)|Wedding Bells]]\" \u2013 3:21\n# \"Lonnie\" \u2013 4:45\n# \"Sale of the Century\" \u2013 4:20\n# \"The Party\" \u2013 8:00\n\n=== Bonus tracks on the 2004 ''Plus'' edition===\n{{Track listing|\n| headline = \n| extra_column = Lead vocals\n| title10 = Power Behind The Throne\n| writer10 = \n| length10 = 3:39\n| extra10 = \n| title11 = Babies\n| writer11 = \n| length11 = 4:42\n| extra11 = \n| title12 = Strange Apparatus\n| writer12 = \n| length12 = 3:53\n| note12 = \"[[An Englishman in New York]]\" single edit\n}}\n\n===Bonus tracks on the 2006 Japanese edition===\n{{Track listing|\n| headline = \n| extra_column = Lead vocals\n| title10 = Power Behind The Throne\n| writer10 = \n| length10 = 3:39\n| extra10 = \n| title11 = Babies\n| writer11 = \n| length11 = 4:42\n| extra11 = \n| title12 = Snack Attack (Extended Version)\n| writer12 = \n| length12 = 6:47\n| extra12 = \n}}\n\n==Personnel==\n\n* [[Kevin Godley]] \u2014 [[vocals]], [[drum kit|drums]], [[percussion instrument|percussion]], [[drum machine]]\n* [[Lol Creme]] \u2014 vocals, [[Bass (guitar)|bass]], [[guitar]], [[keyboard instrument|keyboards]], [[synthesizers]]\n* Bimbo Acock \u2013 [[saxophone]]\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n{{Godley & Creme}}\n\n[[Category:1981 albums]]\n[[Category:Godley & Creme albums]]\n[[Category:New wave albums by English artists]]\n", "text_old": "{{Use British English|date=January 2014}}\n{{